%N A096595 Numbers m with the property that m is an anagram of the digits of the distinct prime factors of m.
%H A096595 Robert G. Wilson v, <a href="/A096595/b096595.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..904</a>
%H A096595 Gil Broussard, <a href="http://home.mindspring.com/~kikiriki/id15.html">Integers Anagrammed by Their Unique Primes</a>.
%F A096595 The digits of the unique prime factors of n appear exactly once within n in any order, accounting for all the digits of n
%e A096595 104392, whose prime factors are 2*2*2*13049, is a term. The digits 2, 1, 3, 0, 4 and 9 appear exactly once within 104392.
